obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42805)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053&sectionId=42805&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Provisions of the Panchayats (Extension to the Scheduled`
  line `Areas) Act, 1996.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42806)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053&sectionId=42806&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, "Scheduled Areas" means the`
  line `Scheduled Areas as referred to in clause (1) of article 244 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42807)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Extension of Part IX of the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053&sectionId=42807&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part IX of the Constitution relating`
  line `to Panchayats are hereby extended to the Scheduled Areas subject to such exceptions and modifications`
  line `as are provided in section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42808)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Exceptions and modifications to Part IX of the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053&sectionId=42808&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained under Part IX of the Constitution, the Legislature of a State shall not make any law under that`
  line `Part which is inconsistent with any of the following features, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a State legislation on the Panchayats that may be made shall be in consonance with the`
  line `customary law, social and religious practices and traditional management practices of community`
  line resources;
  line
  line `(b) a village shall ordinarily consist of a habitation or a group of habitations or a hamlet or a`
  line `group of hamlets comprising a community and managing its affairs in accordance with traditions and`
  line customs;
  line
  line `(c) every village shall have a Gram Sabha consisting of persons whose names are included in the`
  line `electoral rolls for the Panchayat at the village level;`
  line
  line `(d) every Gram Sabha shall be competent to safeguard and preserve the traditions and customs of`
  line `the people, their cultural identity, community resources and the customary mode of dispute`
  line resolution;
  line
  line `(e) every Gram Sabha shall--`
  line
  line `(i) approve the plans, programmes and projects for social and economic development before`
  line `such plans, programmes and projects are taken up for implementation by the Panchayat at the`
  line `village level;`
  line
  line `(ii) be responsible for the identification or selection of persons as beneficiaries under the`
  line `poverty alleviation and other programmes;`
  line
  line `(f) every Panchayat at the village level shall be required to obtain from the Gram Sabha a`
  line `certification of utilisation of funds by that Panchayat for the plans, programmes and projects referred`
  line `to in clause(e);`
  line
  line `(g) the reservation of seats in the Scheduled Areas at every Panchayat shall be in proportion to the`
  line `population of the communities in that Panchayat for whom reservation is sought to be given under`
  line `Part IX of the Constitution:`
  line
  line `Provided that the reservation for the Scheduled Tribes shall not be less than one-half of the total`
  line `number of seats:`
  line
  line `Provided further that all seats of Chairpersons of Panchayats at all levels shall be reserved for the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(h) the State Government may nominate persons belonging to such Scheduled Tribes as have no`
  line `representation in the Panchayat at the intermediate level or the Panchayat at the district level:`
  line
  line `Provided that such nomination shall not exceed one-tenth of the total members to be elected in`
  line `that Panchayat;`
  line
  line `(i) the Gram Sabha or the Panchayats at the appropriate level shall be consulted before making`
  line `the acquisition of land in the Scheduled Areas for development projects and before re-settling or`
  line `rehabilitating persons affected by such projects in the Scheduled Areas; the actual planning and`
  line `implementation of the projects in the Scheduled Areas shall be coordinated at the State level;`
  line
  line `(j) planning and management of minor water bodies in the Scheduled Areas shall be entrusted to`
  line `Panchayats at the appropriate level;`
  line
  line `(k) the recommendations of the Gram Sabha or the Panchayats at the appropriate level shall be`
  line `made mandatory prior to grant of prospecting licence or mining lease for minor minerals in the`
  line `Scheduled Areas;`
  line
  line `(l) the prior recommendation of the Gram Sabha or the Panchayats at the appropriate level shall`
  line `be made mandatory for grant of concession for the exploitation of minor minerals by auction;`
  line
  line `(m) while endowing Panchayats in the Scheduled Areas with such powers and authority as may`
  line `be necessary to enable them to function as institutions of self-government, a State Legislature shall`
  line `ensure that the Panchayats at the appropriate level and the Gram Sabha are endowed specifically`
  line with--
  line
  line `(i) the power to enforce prohibition or to regulate or restrict the sale and consumption of any`
  line intoxicant;
  line
  line `(ii) the ownership of minor forest produce;`
  line
  line `(iii) the power to prevent alienation of land in the Scheduled Areas and to take appropriate`
  line `action to restore any unlawfully alienated land of a Scheduled Tribe;`
  line
  line `(iv) the power to manage village markets by whatever name called;`
  line
  line `(v) the power to exercise control over money lending to the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(vi) the power to exercise control over institutions and functionaries in all social sectors;`
  line
  line `(vii) the power to control over local plans and resources for such plans including tribal subplans;`
  line
  line `(n) the State legislations that may endow Panchayats with powers and authority as may be`
  line `necessary to enable them to function as institutions of self-government shall contain safeguards to`
  line `ensure that Panchayats at the higher level do not assume the powers and authority of any Panchayat at`
  line `the lower level or of the Gram Sabha;`
  line
  line `(o) the State Legislature shall endeavour to follow the pattern of the Sixth Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution while designing the administrative arrangements in the Panchayats at district levels in`
  line `the Scheduled Areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42809)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Continuance of existing laws and Panchayats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053&sectionId=42809&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00007_199640_1517807323053
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in Part IX of the`
  line `Constitution with exceptions and modifications made by this Act, any provision of any law relating to`
  line `Panchayats in force in the Scheduled Areas immediately before the date on which this Act receives the`
  line `assent of the President which is inconsistent with the provisions of Part IX with such exceptions and`
  line `modifications shall continue to be in force until amended or repealed by a competent Legislature or other`
  line `competent authority or until the expiration of one year from the date on which this Act receives the assent`
  line `of the President:`
  line
  line `Provided that all the Panchayats existing immediately before such date shall continue till the`
  line `expiration of their duration unless sooner dissolved by a resolution passed to that effect by the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of that State or, in the case of a State having Legislative Council, by each House of the`
  line `Legislature of that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
